==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helper
<hw>Help"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, helps, aids, assists, or relieves; <as>as, a lay <ex>helper</ex>
in a parish</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou art the <qex>helper</qex> of the fatherless.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
x. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Compassion . . . oftentimes a <qex>helper</qex> of evils.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. H. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helpful</ent>⟦br⟧
